commit.message: Update CHANGES

Unvendor io.h

From OCaml 4.04 onwards, it's installed.

Require at least version 2 of Dune

See https://github.com/ocaml/opam-repository/pull/21352
Document changes for a new release
Upgrade dune lang from 1.0 to 2.0

The internal function 'failwith' is deprecated.

In ocaml.5.00.0+trunk 'failwith' no longer exist, so replace by 'caml_failwith'
Translate license + comment into a complete SPDX license name
Version 0.8.3
Ensure that the OPAM file passes the lint tests
Do not use in_channel_length (not portable on Windows)
Compile the script to select the implementation
Replace Travis and AppVeyor by Github Actions
Update changelog
Specify the name in dune-project

Do not check the terminal state at startup

Fixes https://github.com/Chris00/ANSITerminal/issues/4
Add test to AppVeyor
Remove all workaround in the documentation

Remove the "build" flag on dune

See https://github.com/ocaml/opam-repository/pull/14266
Use ocaml-ci-scripts for Travis
Merge .descr into .opam file
Switch to Dune
Upgrade to opam 2.0
Add a link to the documentation from the README
Add a "doc" field in the opam file
Use topkg for packaging
Adapt Travis script
Only use Windows calls on terminals

Only use ANSI sequences if on TTY (Unix)

Fixes https://github.com/Chris00/ANSITerminal/issues/1
Move choose_implementation into src/
Adapt Appveyor
